!!!MADE FOR LEARNING PURPOSES!!!
Initially I had no plan of getting this project live, the only reason I have added
SQL and API was for more learning!

This project is an early stage backend system designed to explore how decisions can be made safely and
consistently under explicit rules, constraints, and data contracts.
I built this project to practice backend engineering fundamentals state modeling, data validation,
defensive design and reasoning about system behavior under imperfect inputs.
At a high level, the system models decision making as a state machine.

Instead of starting with APIs or databases I wanted to start with logic. My goal was to understand invariants
and boundaries, then built outwards.

This system is structured as a pipeline:
1. DataState
raw inputs are received immediately checked for basic validity
2. EvidenceMapping
Inputs must be transformed into a structured dictionary representing evidence.
Any non-dictionary payload is explicitly rejected to prevent ambiguous state.
3. JustificationGate
Evidence is evaluated against predefined rules. If justification criteria are not met, the decision process halts.
4. PathFeasibility
The justified evidence is transformed into steps to create paths based on dependencies.
5. OutputGate
Only steps that are valid can produce an outcome.

Each stage is intentionally isolated to prevent upstream errors from leaking downstream.
Each component defines what shape of data it accepts.
-During development I found an test case that allowed integers to pass as valid evidence. I fixed this by explicitly
refused non-dictionary inputs at multiple boundaries.

The system models decisions as transitions between known states, rather than a series of ad-hoc conditionals.
Making behavior predictable and testable.

I assume inputs are wrong until proven otherwise. Failures should be loud, early, and informative

This project is:
A learning focused backend system
An exploration of state machine and validation logic
An exploration of SQL and API
A foundation for more complex distributed systems

This project is not:
A product-ready service
A framework or library
An AI or ML system

Current Status
Core state machine implemented
Evidence validation enforced
JustificationGate reject invalid payloads
Unit test focused on failure cases
Introduced SQLite
Introduced Flask API

Plans
Real runs with mock data
Scaling with size (if a million people ran the machine at once)
API endpoints

Backend systems succeed or fail based on decisions users never see. This project reflects how I approach engineering
problems: define constraints, make assumptions explicit, and design systems that fail safely instead of silently.

Stack
Language: Python
Paradigm: Object-Oriented Design
Concepts: State machines, validation, defensive design

